 daycare and its effects on young children, legal issues, and the problem of delinquency and social control. Another chapter deals with the broad pattern of social change and its consequences for children.Several chapters focus on physical aspects of the urban environment; the overall ecological perspective, local neighbourhoods, and housing. The book as a whole identifies the fundamentals of a broad issue of concern and examines their implications for policy, practice, and understanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChild welfare. 0aCity children. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh1 aCatton, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriendly, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagarty, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgson, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevine, Saul V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevine, Saul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMichelson, Ellen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMichelson, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoberts, Ellis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpina, Anna-Rose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZiegler, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757825140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487578251423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487578251.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University